# MASLOW-V1.0 — Cline/Cursor Rules

## Deployment (CRITICAL)
After any code change, deployment requires TWO steps:
1. `git add -A && git commit -m "..."` → commits to GitHub
2. `vercel --prod` → deploys to production

Do NOT assume Vercel auto-deploys. Always run `vercel --prod` explicitly after committing.

## Commit Messages
Do NOT add "Co-Authored-By: Claude" or any Co-Authored-By lines to commit messages.

## General
- MVP first. Do not add unrequested features.
- Always confirm scope before starting large changes.
- Ask before installing new packages.
